{
  "text": "For the photon energy range of hard X-rays at XFELs there have been several techniques proposed and applied for single-shot measurements. At SACLA in Japan, a non-online concept was developed using a focusing plane-elliptical mirror to create a diverging beam, spectrally measured using an analyzer crystal [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . At LCLS in the United States of America, a single bent crystal spectrometer was investigated [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] and applied [CITATION_6] . A similar principle is used for the MID experiment of the European XFEL [CITATION_7] . PSI has developed a focusing transmission grating spectrometer in close collaboration with LCLS [CITATION_8] . As an online device operated at SACLA, a combination of a transmission grating [CITATION_9] and the previous concept [CITATION_10] is integrated in [CITATION_11] . Another approach of employing Reflective Zone Plates was proposed by HZB in Germany [CITATION_12] [CITATION_13] , and its potential applications are further investigated [CITATION_14] [CITATION_15] [CITATION_16] .",
  "correct_citation": {
